    <taskbody>
        <context>You can begin typing text by first selecting a tag in the structure panel. This
            allows you to make sure in exactly what tag you are writing in. </context>
        <steps id="steps_a42_lkc_dp">
            <step>
                <cmd>In the structure panel, double click (so that the tag is bolded and italicized)
                    on the tag in which you would like to type. <image placement="break"
                        href="https://cwrc.ca/islandora/object/cwrc%3Af92b94d5-9b51-45ed-a132-25e9ea82dd4d/datastream/OBJ/view"
                        id="image_fcs_hzm_jp" align="center" width="6in" height="4in"/></cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Once you have selected the tag you want to type in, begin typing.<image
                        placement="break"
                        href="https://cwrc.ca/islandora/object/cwrc%3A8c9c1458-be3e-41ea-b944-560f6f21e57e/datastream/OBJ/view"
                        id="image_yfl_4zm_jp" align="center" width="6in" height="4in"/></cmd>
            </step>
        </steps>
        <result>The text will be entered in the tag you have selected, any content that previously
            existed in that tag will be erased.
